    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a pristine example of sequential twin-turbocharged engineering. The 13B-REW rotary engine exhibits stellar compression, delivering seamless power through the transition from primary to secondary boost. The chassis features lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring exceptional lateral grip and communicative feedback. Meticulously maintained with original vacuum routing and no signs of thermal fatigue, this vehicle offers a pure, analog driving experience. The five-speed short-throw transmission shifts with mechanical precision, rounding out a collector-grade package that is mechanically flawless.",
